---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
import HeadingSmall from "@components/HeadingSmall.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Moneytree | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Moneytree</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Founded in 2012 as one of Japan's first personal finance apps, Moneytree grew to serve over 6.5 million users. Its open banking platform now connects to 2,500+ financial institutions and supports 120 enterprise customers.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I joined as Senior Product Designer in 2016, later becoming Director of Discovery. I led the creation of Moneytree Business (reaching ¥2M ARR in one month), designed the core platform serving enterprise customers, and built white-label solutions for 25 regional banks.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Moneytree Business</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I assembled and led a product team through a six-month 0-1 process to create Moneytree Business. In my role I was responsible for all outcomes and output, whether creative, financial or technical.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Through 30+ interviews with business owners and accountants, we discovered some painful insights. Small businesses were drowning in manual financial tasks, spending 30 hours per week visiting ATMs to confirm transactions and reconciling receipts by hand.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      From these efforts we focused on two core needs, monitoring cashflow and preparing clean data for accountants.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-home-desktop.png"
      alt="Dashboard showing business financial data categorization and cash flow insights."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We iterated constantly on these core features based on regular feedback sessions with businesses from industries like heavy machinery and import goods. By avoiding hypothetical personas and cultivating relationships with early adopters, I understood exactly what they needed.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-cashflow-desktop.png"
      alt="Real-time cash flow visualization with predictive analytics."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-export-desktop.png"
      alt="Data export functionality for seamless accountant collaboration."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The secondary opportunity was categorization. By repurposing Moneytree's existing machine learning technology, new patterns emerged for these business owners. Things they had never seen from their banks or accountants became insights for events like cost reduction and planning new hires.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-categories-desktop.png"
      alt="Machine learning-powered transaction categorization revealing spending patterns."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <!-- <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-account-desktop.png"
      alt="Multi-account overview connecting 2,500+ financial institutions."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    /> -->
  </Group>
  <!-- <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We chose not to build a responsive product at launch, even though we
      added it shortly after. This decision was controversial internally but
      made sense strategically.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I made the call based on what we knew. Most of the business owners we
      spoke with were looking for ways to avoid leaving their place of business.
      They worked at desks, not on phones.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-business-mobile.png"
      alt="Mobile-optimized experience for on-the-go business management."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group> -->
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Only a month after its launch the product hit ¥2M ARR and maintained
      strong growth, surpassing revenue of previous efforts into small business
      products. The company's renewed focus on small businesses also opened up
      interesting new partnerships, including a lending product with a major
      credit card company.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      When MUFG Bank, Ltd. acquired Moneytree in 2025, they specifically cited
      Moneytree Business growth as one of the reasons they were confident and
      excited about the purchase.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Moneytree LINK</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Moneytree LINK was one of Japan's first Open Banking platforms, setting
      the blueprint for financial data legislation in the country and enabling
      secure financial connectivity for millions of users.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Think Plaid, but built specifically for Japan's unique financial
      ecosystem.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We provided data aggregation services and sharing infrastructure that
      allowed fintech startups, lending companies, insurance firms, and major
      institutions including MUFG, Mizuho, SMBC, AMEX, and Norton to offer you
      seamless financial experiences.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <HeadingSmall class="px-2">Moneytree ID</HeadingSmall>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Known as the core of Moneytree LINK, this product combined three key
      components: a REST API, native SDKs, and two web interfaces. Together,
      they embodied our vision of data-portability in an Open Banking world. It
      provided users a way to connect their financial accounts, control exactly
      what data you shared, and enabled our customers to receive that
      information seamlessly for better financial services.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-vault.png"
      alt="Secure data vault for financial institution connectivity."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-service.png"
      alt="Enterprise banking API management and monitoring tools."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      To meet enterprise customer requirements while building trust with end
      users, we implemented extensive customization options. These included
      custom colors, logos, and text, as well as control over which financial
      institutions and accounts could be added, allowing major institutions to
      maintain their brand identity.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-fast-onboarding.png"
      alt="Optimized onboarding reducing setup time from minutes to seconds."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-fast-onboarding-branded.png"
      alt="White-label onboarding experience for enterprise partners."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Isshou Tsucho</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Before Moneytree LINK became our flagship strategy, we created bespoke
      white-label experiences for regional banks in Japan. Known in English as
      the 'Lifetime Bankbook', these solutions addressed a growing market
      challenge.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Regional banks were struggling with digital transformation. Market forces
      were pushing financial services to adopt better digital practices, while
      rural-to-urban migration left regional banks losing customers to national
      banks with superior digital offerings.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Working with Bank of Yokohama as our first customer, I designed a mobile
      banking product (alongside two engineers) that had to integrate with
      official banking APIs rather than our usual data scraping approach. This
      technical constraint required careful design considerations to maintain
      user trust while working within API limitations.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I focused on creating an interface that felt familiar to regional bank
      customers while providing core digital banking functions—balance checking,
      transaction history, and spending insights—through a seamless mobile web
      experience.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/moneytree-link-isshou-tsucho.png"
      alt="Isshou Tsucho bank integration showcasing API versatility."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The "drop-in" solution gave regional banks digital banking capabilities
      that matched their national competitors. Users could check balances, view
      transactions, and track spending through an interface that maintained each
      bank's identity.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The project's success led to partnerships with 25 regional banks and
      eventually caught the attention of Japan's major national banks,
      validating our white-label approach.
    </Text>
  </Group>
</Layout>
